Hi @jhseu

Yes,  The enum is under a separate namespace. But, OPAQUE in Windows.h is a macro. macro comes first. It's like:
```c
#define OPAQUE              2
enum something{
  a,
  b,
  OPAQUE,  //here, you will get an error, no matter which namespace the enum lives
};
```
